HEADWORD: long-drawn-out
<hw>long-drawn-out</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>relatively long
in duration; <as>as, a <ex>long-drawn-out</ex> visit from my
mother-in-law</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> drawn-out, extended, prolonged,
protracted.</syn>⟦br⟧
